The paper deals with quantum communication complexity and its relationship with classical communication complexity, which falls under the category of computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of quantum mechanics in communication suggests that it may also fall under the category of quantum information (cs.QI). The paper also involves lower bounds and polynomial threshold degree, which are topics in data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the pattern tensor method, which is a tool used in machine learning (cs.LG).
